trans-unit.source: Exception occurs if columns with the same name is not allowed.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs if columns with the same name is not allowed.

trans-unit.source: Exception occurs if multiple columns have the same name.
trans-unit.target: Exception occurs if multiple columns have the same name.

trans-unit.source: One way you may receive this error is if the dataset does not have a header row and column names are automatically assigned: Col0, Col1, etc.
trans-unit.target: One way you may receive this error is if the dataset does not have a header row and column names are automatically assigned: Col0, Col1, etc.

trans-unit.source: If columns have same name, insert a <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> module between the input dataset and the module.
trans-unit.target: If columns have same name, insert a <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> module between the input dataset and the module.

trans-unit.source: Use the column selector in <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> to select columns to rename, typing the new names into the <ui>New column names</ui> textbox.
trans-unit.target: Use the column selector in <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link> to select columns to rename, typing the new names into the <ui>New column names</ui> textbox.

trans-unit.source: Equal column names are specified in arguments.
trans-unit.target: Equal column names are specified in arguments.

trans-unit.source: Equal column names are not allowed by module.
trans-unit.target: Equal column names are not allowed by module.

trans-unit.source: Equal column names in arguments "{0}" and "{1}" are not allowed.
trans-unit.target: Equal column names in arguments "{0}" and "{1}" are not allowed.
